rComments: We gave her feed back to help us do better, and she basically said she wouldn't do it. Disliked the course,  way to boring.  I attended every class and it was brutal.
She is not approachable. Unhelpful and not clear in her lectures. The material didn't seem to suit the topic of the class.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Great Professor. Passionate about her topic. Very knowledgeable. Yes, she talks fast, but she will explain anything clearly if you ask. Overall, this was one of the best courses I've taken at Laurier

Talks too fast. If you don't go to lectures you'll be a little bit screwed as her readings are kind of hard but she explains it all in class. Her tests are actually really easy tho, which makes the course easy because she gives you the questions before the midterms/exams so you know exactly what to expect and can prep your answer. Not bad overall!

Prof came off a bit unorganized at times. There were moments when I questioned what I was getting out of lecture but generally when it came time for exams everything seemed to come together. I liked the course but I am not sure I'd chose to take one of her classes again.
really nice. really easy if you read the material.
